respectively. As the BE for two sister nuclei is always smaller than for two non-sister nuclei, these two values predict that cell 2, 3 are sister cells, and cell 1, 4 are sister cells respectively. Table 3.3 The bending energies of one four-cell clone in HMEC cell line.
