However, in some cases, it is difficult to identify sister cell and cousin cell pairs in cell clones by Bending Energy. For example, in Table 3.5, for HMEC cell clone No. 6, among the 6 BE values, it is difficult to judge that the cell 1, 2 are sister cells or cell 1, 3 are sister cells because both pairs have smaller BE values. In this case, the judgement also depends on visualization. The comparison of sister cells generally yields a smaller bending energy than the comparison of cousin cells. The judgement based on bending energies is more reliable compared to distance and angle measurements, although Bending Energy can not identify sister cell and cousin cell pairs for all clones absolutely. It will be interesting to test how accurately BE can identify sister and cousin cell pairs. Table 3.5 The BE comparison in the HMEC 4-cell clone No. 6.
