3.4.3 DD result in every cell line

In order to compare the CT arrangement of two cells in a simpler way, the difference between the distances of the geometric centers of corresponding points in every two cells was calculated. For the sake of simplicity, only the distances between homologues of the same chromosome in every cell were taken into account. In order to compare the different cell stages (Generation I-VI), the mean over all DD values inside one generation was taken as the DD of this cell stage.
